The paper deals with an algorithmic problem related to finding the longest increasing subsequence in an array, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a randomized algorithm that estimates the length of the LIS in polylogarithmic time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, given the focus on algorithmic techniques and complexity analysis, cs.DS and cs.IT seem to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.LG.
